Thorax
. 22 thorax segments, of these 20 "complete" and two "incomplete" (
Fig. 7d
); dorsal spines beginning at 9th thorax segment, twelve thorax segments with dorsal spines; one dorsal spine at each thorax segment, first dorsal spine smaller than following one, last dorsal spine smaller than preceding one; last "complete" thorax segment with dorsal spine (
Fig. 7d
).

Head
. Section between condyle and external eye contour concave or straight; eye bulge absent or present, if present large, compound eye oval or round; acute or obtuse to straight angle between head and rostrum; anterior margin of rostrum straight or convex, transition between anterior and ventral margin rounded or angular (
Fig. 8a
). Antennule with 15–23 lobules, closely or widely arranged (
Fig. 8b
); reaches to 9th –13th antennary segment. Antenna with 12–15 antennary segments, middle antennary segment anteriorly with four to seven spines (

Fig. 
8g

).

Thorax
. 20–23 thorax segments, of these 18–21 "complete" and one or two "incomplete" (
Fig. 8d
); dorsal spines beginning at 8th –10th thorax segment, 9–13 thorax segments with dorsal spines; last dorsal spine smaller than or same size as preceding one, last "complete" thorax segment with or without dorsal spine (
Fig. 8d
).
